<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-02T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-02T12:00:00-05:00" n="224" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/978.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-02T12:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1912—12
                                    noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your July 1.</p>
                            <p>The Department concurs with the British Government in its view that
                                loans to China should not be made without adequate provisions for
                                supervision of expenditures. You may join your colleagues in
                                representations to that effect. By “adequate provisions for
                                supervision” the Department has in mind substantially the bases of
                                the bankers’ telegram of May 15 without insistence upon the
                                financial agency.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>